<p>Downtown Newark's historic district requires special consideration for solar installations due to architectural preservation guidelines, though ground-mount systems may be viable for properties with adequate yard space. The Paper Mill Road corridor features many ranch-style homes ideal for solar installations, with simple roof geometries and minimal shading concerns. Suburban developments like Harmony Hills and Nottingham Green typically offer excellent solar potential with newer construction standards that accommodate modern HVAC systems efficiently. Each neighborhood's proximity to the University of Delaware campus influences energy usage patterns, with some areas experiencing seasonal occupancy variations that affect optimal system sizing.</p>

